rtresses. The influx of tourists with links either directly or indirectly to the war took hold and continues to play a significant economic role in Normandy and elsewhere. As France moved from wartime to a postwar era of reconciliation and European Union, memory tourism has held strong and exerts significant influence across the country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCollective memoryzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aDark tourismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aGermansxTravelzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aHeritage tourismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aTourismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aWar and societyzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zFrance. 4aEurope. 4aHistory. 4aJewish Studies.  aHitler, World War II France, postwar memory tourism, humanize war, Popular Front legislation of 1936.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501715891?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501715891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501715891/original  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEB